Rating: 4
This was wonderful! The pineapple salsa is a great accompaniment to any seafood dish if made properly. Be sure to finely mince your red onion; I used about a 1/2 cup. Also, don't add any more cilantro than called for. The recipe calls for 1/2 pineapple cut into 12 slices; to get 12 slices at 1/2 inch thick, I needed a full pineapple. And be sure to use fresh pineapple, not canned. We liked this recipe so much, we grilled fresh tuna the next night to have with the salsa. It was fantastic!

Rating: 4
We were looking for a simple recipe for dinner and chose this, it was very easy to make. The only deviations I made was to add fresh garlic to the grilling mixture to add some flavor, cut the pineapple into very small chunks so not to dwarf the other salsa ingredients, and added more Jalapeño for my taste. The meal was great, I had some Knorr brand lemon and jasmine rice and Santa Margherita Pinot Grigio on hand. which went perfectly with the meal! My guest Loved it, I will make this again!

Rating: 3
If you cut back the red onion to 1/4 cup and finely mince it, this is a really good dish. To make up for the lesser amount of onion, I added a half diced avacado and a half diced nectarine I had left over from the day before. REally good. Also, I grilled the pineapple in wedges instead of rings for easier turning, and the leftovers we had had for dessert (don't salt & pepper them before cooking) with Hagen Daz caramel ice cream. Wow.

